e.\n\nA quiet nature image follows: a shallow stream or garden waterway runs between rocks and plants, with sunlight reflecting on the rippling surface. This dissolves into a tall, clear glass filled with a sparkling, colorless drink and ice cubes. Tiny bubbles rise densely through the liquid. Soft pink and red blossoms blur around the glass, framing it like flowers in the foreground.\n\nThe view returns to close-ups of blossoms: a pink flower on a dark branch, glossy petals catching the light, with a round red bud nearby. The flower fills the scene, then a Sprite bottle overlaps it visually. The hand holding the bottle is pale, and the label is again clear: “Sprite” in dark letters on the white shield, with the starburst. Condensation dots the glass.\n\nA white drinking straw appears inserted into the open mouth of a Sprite bottle. The bottle neck is tilted diagonally upward, and the straw leans out at an angle. Behind it, large pale flower petals and warm colors blur softly, keeping the spring-flower motif around the drink.\n\nMore branches covered in white blossoms appear. The flowers cluster on thin stems, with small buds spaced along the twigs. Behind the branches, a child gradually comes into view through the flowers. He is a young boy with short brown hair, wearing light green overalls over a pale short-sleeved shirt. He sits outdoors among yellow flowers and greenery, looking down at a Sprite bottle in front of him. He holds the bottle near his lap and appears to use or remove a straw.\n\nThe final close-ups focus on the boy’s face and the bottle. He looks down with a serious, concentrated expression, then raises the Sprite bottle to his mouth. The bottle label is partly visible as he grips it with both hands. He drinks directly from the bottle, tilting it upward until the dark round base of the bottle faces outward. His eyes widen slightly as he drinks, framed by the blurred yellow flowers behind him.",
